Here are the direct download sources for common operating systems:
Operating System 
	Download Link	Notes
Ubuntu	https://cloud-images.ubuntu.com/releases/	Look for files ending in .img (QCOW2 format). Minimal images are also available.
Debian	https://cdimage.debian.org/images/cloud/	The "Plain VM" or "generic" images are best for local QEMU use.
Fedora	https://fedoraproject.org/cloud/	Provides a "Cloud Base" image optimized for cloud environments.
AlmaLinux	https://wiki.almalinux.org/cloud/Generic-cloud-on-local	Offers generic cloud images for testing and development.
CirrOS	https://docs.openstack.org/image-guide/obtain-images.html	A minimal test image for OpenStack, useful for quick QEMU testing.

custom / special

windows https://cloudbase.it/windows-cloud-images/


